        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 8:57PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 857 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 18 miles northeast of San Jon to 6
miles northeast of Clovis, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clovis, Logan, San Jon, Grady, Broadview, Wheatland, Bellview,
Ranchvale, Bard and Pleasant Hill.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 351 and 373.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
